other_tests.procedure_name: Ultrasound (UNILAT UP EXT VEINS US RIGHT)
other_tests.findings: The right internal jugular vein does not compress nor does it demonstrate flow. There is possibly echogenic material within it, concerning for thrombus. Comparison to the left side demonstrates flow within the left internal jugular vein. A catheter is partially imaged within the right subclavian vein; flow is demonstrated within the right subclavian vein. The right cephalic vein is not seen. The right axillary vein demonstrates normal compressibility and flow. The right brachial vein containing the PICC demonstrates flow.
